1
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:08,925
Excuse me. I just gotta get by.
Sorry. Excuse me.

2
00:00:09,009 --> 00:00:11,553
Coming through.
Excuse me, sorry. Pardon me.

3
00:00:11,636 --> 00:00:13,555
Excuse me, please. Sorry. Thank you.

4
00:00:23,815 --> 00:00:25,567
Right this way, please! Thank you!

5
00:00:25,650 --> 00:00:27,318
MS. KAZUKO HOSOKI
SIX-STAR ASTROLOGY LECTURE

6
00:00:27,402 --> 00:00:30,447
Your name, please? Just so I can see
if we've got your name down here, ma'am.

7
00:00:31,239 --> 00:00:34,159
Yes, sir. So the fee
is going to be 10,000 yen, please.

8
00:00:34,242 --> 00:00:36,703
Ms. Hosoki's new book is now available.

9
00:00:36,786 --> 00:00:38,288
We've got copies right here, folks!

10
00:00:38,371 --> 00:00:41,207
- That'll be 4,000 yen.
- Come look and get a fresh copy!

11
00:00:41,291 --> 00:00:44,127
We only have a limited supply here.
Don't miss your chance.

12
00:00:44,210 --> 00:00:47,714
They sell out fast.
Learn the latest about Six-Star Astrology!

13
00:00:47,797 --> 00:00:50,008
- And you're requesting a private reading?
- Yes.

14
00:00:50,091 --> 00:00:52,594
- That will be an additional 100,000 yen.
- Oh, okay.

15
00:00:52,677 --> 00:00:54,929
- Mm-hmm.
- Here you are.

16
00:00:55,513 --> 00:00:58,058
- Thank you. I appreciate it.
- Of course. Have a nice day.

17
00:00:58,141 --> 00:01:02,353
<i>Kazuko Hosoki is</i>
<i>the most famous fortune teller in Japan.</i>

18
00:01:03,354 --> 00:01:06,941
<i>No matter how much money she earns</i>
<i>from her television appearances or books,</i>

19
00:01:07,025 --> 00:01:10,779
<i>the main pillar of her massive income</i>
<i>comes from her fortune-telling.</i>

20
00:01:11,446 --> 00:01:14,908
All of you gathered here today
want to know the future.

21
00:01:14,991 --> 00:01:18,203
You want to change your present.
You want to find happiness.

22
00:01:18,703 --> 00:01:20,413
You all know who I am.

23
00:01:22,874 --> 00:01:25,043
You all know that I've made my career

24
00:01:25,126 --> 00:01:28,588
making countless predictions
through Six-Star Astrology.

25
00:01:28,671 --> 00:01:30,423
That's why you're here.

26
00:01:30,507 --> 00:01:34,427
You want to master Six-Star Astrology
just like I have.

27
00:01:34,928 --> 00:01:36,054
Am I right?

28
00:01:38,723 --> 00:01:42,018
The problem for those of you who nodded
is that you're embarrassingly ignorant!

29
00:01:43,520 --> 00:01:47,690
What truly matters most is how we choose
to live our lives, is it not?

30
00:01:52,112 --> 00:01:56,282
I see a few people here roughly my age.

31
00:01:58,201 --> 00:02:01,663
When we were children,
it wasn't all fun and games.

32
00:02:01,746 --> 00:02:04,666
We were constantly
on the brink of starvation.

33
00:02:05,667 --> 00:02:08,461
Being so focused
on just surviving each day,

34
00:02:08,545 --> 00:02:12,340
we couldn't even imagine what the future
looked like beyond our next meal.

35
00:02:12,423 --> 00:02:13,424
Remember?

36
00:02:15,135 --> 00:02:17,095
At least, that's the way it was for me.

37
00:02:18,471 --> 00:02:22,559
And even as an adult woman,
I continued to fail repeatedly.

38
00:02:23,101 --> 00:02:25,228
I went through unbearable suffering.

39
00:02:26,354 --> 00:02:28,982
There were even times I attempted suicide.

40
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:32,652
I never thought
to ask myself the question,

41
00:02:32,735 --> 00:02:34,779
"What is the right way to live?"

42
00:02:36,573 --> 00:02:38,158
But then, soon after,

43
00:02:38,658 --> 00:02:41,119
I found Six-Star Astrology.

44
00:02:41,202 --> 00:02:44,539
I studied like my life depended on it
and was reborn from it.

45
00:02:45,123 --> 00:02:47,959
You can always change your life.

46
00:02:49,586 --> 00:02:53,381
<i>It constantly amazes me</i>
<i>how many people are drawn in by her words.</i>

47
00:02:53,464 --> 00:02:55,091
…you'll become all the wiser for it.

48
00:02:55,175 --> 00:02:58,803
<i>It's almost as if she's the leader</i>
<i>of some kind of religious cult.</i>

49
00:03:01,222 --> 00:03:04,309
Your son is over 40 years old
and shut in at home.

50
00:03:04,392 --> 00:03:07,687
And on top of all that,
he's been violent towards the family.

51
00:03:07,770 --> 00:03:09,105
Yes.

52
00:03:09,189 --> 00:03:10,690
You know why that is?

53
00:03:10,773 --> 00:03:14,360
It's because you don't value your family
as you should.

54
00:03:14,861 --> 00:03:16,988
Nor have you treated them
with the respect they deserve.

55
00:03:17,071 --> 00:03:19,365
- It was never my intention.
- Your intentions mean nothing!

56
00:03:20,408 --> 00:03:24,162
Nothing in our lives or in this world
is more important than our family.

57
00:03:24,787 --> 00:03:27,790
Have you been practicing
proper memorial rites?

58
00:03:28,374 --> 00:03:29,375
No.

59
00:03:30,251 --> 00:03:33,254
So what you're telling me
is you've neglected your ancestors,

60
00:03:33,338 --> 00:03:35,465
yet still have the nerve
to say you're unhappy.

61
00:03:35,548 --> 00:03:37,050
That's incredibly selfish.

62
00:03:38,176 --> 00:03:39,344
I'm so sorry.

63
00:03:44,098 --> 00:03:45,308
However,

64
00:03:46,392 --> 00:03:48,144
you do possess the hands of a hard worker.

65
00:03:48,228 --> 00:03:49,062
What?

66
00:03:49,562 --> 00:03:52,023
They're calloused,
just like my mother's hands.

67
00:03:55,902 --> 00:03:57,570
It'll all work out.

68
00:03:57,654 --> 00:04:00,323
So don't worry.
Your efforts will be rewarded.

69
00:04:00,406 --> 00:04:04,953
But you need to start by performing
the proper ancestral memorial rites.

70
00:04:05,745 --> 00:04:08,039
Then you'll need to build a grave too.

71
00:04:08,581 --> 00:04:10,667
Starting with that is mandatory.

72
00:04:11,501 --> 00:04:12,794
Understood?

73
00:04:14,545 --> 00:04:15,922
I understand.

74
00:04:17,006 --> 00:04:18,633
Hosoki-sensei.

75
00:04:19,175 --> 00:04:21,052
I can't thank you enough.

76
00:04:23,263 --> 00:04:25,515
MOONLIGHT, 11.2 MILLION YEN
VENUS, 9.8 MILLION YEN

77
00:04:25,598 --> 00:04:28,977
<i>There are nasty rumors</i>
<i>that she receives some kickback or cut</i>

78
00:04:29,060 --> 00:04:30,812
<i>from the gravestone dealers she endorses.</i>

79
00:04:31,479 --> 00:04:32,438
<i>Worse than that,</i>

80
00:04:32,522 --> 00:04:35,149
<i>many have accused her</i>
<i>of engaging in scams and fraud.</i>

81
00:04:39,112 --> 00:04:42,740
<i>And yet, the overwhelming majority</i>
<i>of the mainstream media</i>

82
00:04:42,824 --> 00:04:45,201
<i>completely ignore these accusations.</i>

83
00:04:45,285 --> 00:04:46,953
<i>And the simple reason for that is</i>

84
00:04:47,036 --> 00:04:49,747
<i>Kazuko Hosoki brings in a lot of money.</i>

85
00:05:08,891 --> 00:05:12,478
You've got that doe-eyed look of someone
wondering how I make so much money.

86
00:05:12,562 --> 00:05:14,647
Some say
you're nothing more than a con artist

87
00:05:14,731 --> 00:05:16,983
taking advantage
of the easily manipulated.

88
00:05:17,066 --> 00:05:19,485
I can tell you're judging these people.

89
00:05:20,069 --> 00:05:22,530
But if you asked anyone
who came here today,

90
00:05:23,031 --> 00:05:26,117
they'd tell you they were thrilled
to pay to hear me talk.

91
00:05:32,415 --> 00:05:35,126
I'm curious
about your thoughts though, Minori.

92
00:05:36,294 --> 00:05:39,339
Honestly, I'm not interested
in fortune-telling,

93
00:05:40,089 --> 00:05:42,258
but your speech was powerful,

94
00:05:42,342 --> 00:05:46,179
or, at least,
there was something convincing about it.

95
00:05:46,763 --> 00:05:47,597
It was--

96
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:50,641
It was powerful
because I've been through hell.

97
00:05:58,983 --> 00:06:02,862
How are you able to earn so much money,
Ms. Hosoki?

98
00:06:02,945 --> 00:06:04,322
What do you think?

99
00:06:05,907 --> 00:06:08,826
Well, you lived through financial burdens,

100
00:06:08,910 --> 00:06:11,371
so you understand the value of money.

101
00:06:11,871 --> 00:06:13,915
What <i>is </i>the value of money?

102
00:06:18,127 --> 00:06:19,379
Give me your wallet.

103
00:06:19,879 --> 00:06:22,006
- What?
- Your wallet. Hand it over.

104
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:22,965
Oh.

105
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:37,021
Not much there, huh?

106
00:07:30,116 --> 00:07:31,784
No, stop that!

107
00:07:32,493 --> 00:07:35,538
Please, that's…
that's all our grocery money. We need it.

108
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:40,585
Bring me 20,000 yen.

109
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:47,216
Here you are, ma'am.

110
00:07:48,801 --> 00:07:51,471
It was worth the 20,000 yen

111
00:07:51,971 --> 00:07:56,350
just to see that panicked look
come across your face.

112
00:08:02,148 --> 00:08:04,233
The true value of money

113
00:08:04,734 --> 00:08:06,694
is the price of desire.

114
00:08:07,945 --> 00:08:10,031
Whatever form that should take.

115
00:08:10,114 --> 00:08:13,159
Desire to fill an empty stomach,
to wear something beautiful,

116
00:08:13,242 --> 00:08:16,662
to succeed in your field,
or to escape from misery.

117
00:08:17,538 --> 00:08:19,916
Desire's a chameleon that way.

118
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:26,172
And fortune-telling
shows people the path to their desires.

119
00:08:26,255 --> 00:08:28,049
That's how I make money.

120
00:08:31,802 --> 00:08:33,721
What do you desire, Minori?

121
00:08:35,181 --> 00:08:36,182
Desire?

122
00:08:43,606 --> 00:08:46,275
Hmm. You're coming out with me tonight.

123
00:08:49,111 --> 00:08:52,156
All right, I'm pleased to present
our lovely queen over here.

124
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:54,325
- Yeah! Yeah!
- Our premium champagne!

125
00:08:54,408 --> 00:08:55,660
- Dom Perignon!
- Yeah!

126
00:08:55,743 --> 00:08:57,787
Are you all ready for this?

127
00:08:57,870 --> 00:09:01,666
This one's for the media queen
and everybody's favorite fortune teller!

128
00:09:01,749 --> 00:09:03,459
- Let's hear a hurrah!
- Hurrah!

129
00:09:03,543 --> 00:09:05,253
Love to you all!

130
00:09:05,336 --> 00:09:07,004
Let's go!

131
00:09:07,088 --> 00:09:09,215
- Thank you for those kind words!
- Yeah!

132
00:09:09,298 --> 00:09:12,677
So let's keep drinking and bopping
till we drop dead!

133
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:13,636
- Hurrah!
- Hurrah!

134
00:09:13,719 --> 00:09:14,887
- Hurrah!
- Hurrah!

135
00:09:14,971 --> 00:09:16,847
Our queen tonight is the greatest!

136
00:09:16,931 --> 00:09:19,809
So let's raise
a glass of champagne and drink!

137
00:09:19,892 --> 00:09:22,311
- Bottoms up! Let's go! Let's go!
- Yeah! Yeah!

138
00:09:22,395 --> 00:09:24,313
- Let's go! Dom Perignon!
- Cheers!

139
00:09:24,397 --> 00:09:26,857
We'll be drinking all night long!

140
00:09:26,941 --> 00:09:29,569
Let's go! Whoo!

141
00:09:33,114 --> 00:09:34,323
Minori-chan.

142
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:37,034
Here.

143
00:09:37,618 --> 00:09:39,704
Whoo!

144
00:09:39,787 --> 00:09:41,080
Everybody!

145
00:09:41,163 --> 00:09:43,541
We're going extra hard
with this cutie tonight!

146
00:09:47,545 --> 00:09:48,546
Come on, Minori.

147
00:09:48,629 --> 00:09:51,424
Stop being so uptight
and let yourself go for once!

148
00:09:56,095 --> 00:09:57,430
Come on, down it.

149
00:09:57,513 --> 00:09:59,056
Chug, chug, chug!

150
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:00,391
Nicely done.

151
00:10:00,474 --> 00:10:01,517
That's not done. Go on.

152
00:10:01,601 --> 00:10:02,852
Yeah.

153
00:10:02,935 --> 00:10:03,853
That's it.

154
00:10:04,353 --> 00:10:06,314
We'll have to get you a refill now.

155
00:10:10,776 --> 00:10:13,446
All right, everyone! Here we go!

156
00:10:13,529 --> 00:10:14,864
Our little princess is up!

157
00:10:14,947 --> 00:10:16,782
Chug! Chug! Chug!

158
00:10:16,866 --> 00:10:18,534
Chug! Chug! Chug!

159
00:10:18,618 --> 00:10:20,328
Chug! Chug! Chug!

160
00:10:20,411 --> 00:10:24,290
Everyone, grab a glass! Bottoms up!

161
00:10:28,919 --> 00:10:31,005
Having a blast or what?

162
00:10:31,088 --> 00:10:32,381
Yeah, it's so great!

163
00:10:35,551 --> 00:10:37,970
You haven't gotten laid in a little while,
have you?

164
00:10:38,596 --> 00:10:39,555
Huh?

165
00:10:40,765 --> 00:10:42,767
You can fix that here, ya know?

166
00:10:48,230 --> 00:10:52,068
For the right amount,
you can treat men like toys.

167
00:11:02,411 --> 00:11:04,455
It is here that I get

168
00:11:05,122 --> 00:11:07,208
my revenge on men.

169
00:11:21,764 --> 00:11:26,102
<i>It is with great honor,</i>
<i>profound gratitude, and heartfelt joy</i>

170
00:11:26,185 --> 00:11:30,106
<i>that I present to you</i>
<i>the opening of the Japan World Exposition.</i>

171
00:11:30,189 --> 00:11:32,608
<i>As the boom years came to an end,</i>

172
00:11:32,692 --> 00:11:36,153
<i>the cracks beneath</i>
<i>the rapid growth began to show.</i>

173
00:11:38,322 --> 00:11:42,743
<i>Behind the veil of prosperity,</i>
<i>stagnation is always lurking.</i>

174
00:11:42,827 --> 00:11:45,162
<i>And inside that stagnation,</i>

175
00:11:46,831 --> 00:11:48,874
<i>knee-deep in its clutches,</i>

176
00:11:49,875 --> 00:11:50,918
<i>was me.</i>

177
00:11:56,590 --> 00:11:58,884
We shall now commence the ceremony

178
00:11:58,968 --> 00:12:01,762
between Genichi Kawashima-dono,

179
00:12:02,888 --> 00:12:05,850
the underboss of the Dainihon Kosei-kai,

180
00:12:06,475 --> 00:12:08,644
and Ittetsu Endo-dono,

181
00:12:09,145 --> 00:12:11,689
the underboss of the Nishin-kai,

182
00:12:12,940 --> 00:12:17,069
known as
the fifty-fifty brotherhood cup ritual.

183
00:12:17,695 --> 00:12:19,655
I invite both these gentlemen

184
00:12:20,489 --> 00:12:23,492
to seal their fifty-fifty brotherhood vow
at once.

185
00:12:24,076 --> 00:12:27,329
Once it is firmly set,
please drink your cups

186
00:12:27,955 --> 00:12:29,832
in a single draft

187
00:12:30,332 --> 00:12:32,209
and place them inside your kimono.

188
00:12:50,060 --> 00:12:53,814
And now, I bring this ritual to a close.

189
00:12:54,857 --> 00:12:56,317
Your hands, gentlemen.

190
00:13:08,954 --> 00:13:10,372
<i>So, listen.</i>

191
00:13:10,456 --> 00:13:11,582
The other day,

192
00:13:11,665 --> 00:13:14,543
my grandkid begged me to go to the expo.

193
00:13:14,627 --> 00:13:17,546
And the place was packed as all hell.
There were lines everywhere.

194
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:20,257
Ah, maybe you should've fired
a couple warning shots.

195
00:13:20,341 --> 00:13:22,051
- You'd have cleared the whole place out.
- Ah!

196
00:13:22,134 --> 00:13:25,137
You can imagine I thought of that,
but not in front of the kid, you know?

197
00:13:26,222 --> 00:13:29,141
The famous Takiguchi
worried for his granddaughter.

198
00:13:29,225 --> 00:13:31,101
I guess he really has gone soft.

199
00:13:31,769 --> 00:13:34,396
The old you
would've had his gun out in a second.

200
00:13:43,781 --> 00:13:47,159
That Takiguchi bastard's
been getting real cocky lately.

201
00:13:47,827 --> 00:13:49,328
I guess he's doing well?

202
00:13:50,204 --> 00:13:51,997
His income's been real steady.

203
00:13:52,957 --> 00:13:54,333
From that Akasaka place?

204
00:13:54,416 --> 00:13:55,334
Yeah.

205
00:13:55,835 --> 00:13:58,337
He used some scammer to con this woman,

206
00:13:58,838 --> 00:14:00,714
and they seized her business.

207
00:14:01,340 --> 00:14:02,800
She was a big player in Ginza, right?

208
00:14:04,260 --> 00:14:06,554
Apparently, he seduced her,
made her his mistress,

209
00:14:06,637 --> 00:14:08,180
and they kept the place running.

210
00:14:08,264 --> 00:14:10,808
He completely drained her.
All for sex and money.

211
00:14:11,308 --> 00:14:13,227
What kind of scumbag does that?

212
00:14:14,562 --> 00:14:15,896
I heard a rumor

213
00:14:16,438 --> 00:14:19,817
Takiguchi's in the business
of dealing crystals.

214
00:14:19,900 --> 00:14:21,694
I thought that was off-limits
in the Kosei-kai.

215
00:14:21,777 --> 00:14:23,946
Yeah, well, they're keeping it
under wraps for now.

216
00:14:24,738 --> 00:14:28,659
Word of mouth is that Takiguchi himself
has been hitting it hard.

217
00:14:29,159 --> 00:14:31,704
What else would you expect from a scumbag?

218
00:14:33,581 --> 00:14:34,832
Not just that.

219
00:14:35,499 --> 00:14:39,378
He has also… been messing around
on our turf.

220
00:14:40,462 --> 00:14:44,925
But… in light
of our boss's brotherhood pledge,

221
00:14:45,009 --> 00:14:47,094
we can't go anywhere near the guy.

222
00:14:48,554 --> 00:14:50,806
That guy's a real issue.

223
00:14:53,058 --> 00:14:54,310
Isn't he, Hotta?

224
00:15:07,907 --> 00:15:09,658
- Please follow me.
- Mm-hmm.

225
00:15:11,493 --> 00:15:13,370
- It's just down here. Not much further.
- Wow.

226
00:15:13,454 --> 00:15:15,039
It's beautiful in here.

227
00:15:15,122 --> 00:15:16,248
That's kind.

228
00:15:16,332 --> 00:15:18,208
Seriously. This place is gorgeous.

229
00:15:18,292 --> 00:15:20,002
- Look at that.
- Just this way.

230
00:15:20,085 --> 00:15:22,087
- Thank you for bringing me here.
- Welcome.

231
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:25,341
- Allow me to take your things.
- Thank you very much.

232
00:15:25,424 --> 00:15:26,842
Your table is just this way.

233
00:16:24,316 --> 00:16:25,818
Thank you for coming in.

234
00:16:29,822 --> 00:16:32,408
Please, take care,
and have a good evening.

235
00:16:45,170 --> 00:16:46,672
Did Takiguchi go?

236
00:16:46,755 --> 00:16:49,550
Uh, I think he's here somewhere.

237
00:16:51,385 --> 00:16:55,723
Excuse me, uh, the boss
would like a word with you in the back.

238
00:16:55,806 --> 00:16:57,474
What for?

239
00:16:57,558 --> 00:16:58,642
I don't know.

240
00:16:59,351 --> 00:17:00,936
He just told me to get you.

241
00:17:14,491 --> 00:17:21,373
<i>The place I arrived at</i>

242
00:17:22,499 --> 00:17:28,047
<i>Was in New Orleans</i>

243
00:17:29,423 --> 00:17:36,055
<i>It was a brothel</i>

244
00:17:36,722 --> 00:17:43,395
<i>Called the Rising Sun</i>

245
00:18:00,579 --> 00:18:06,293
<i>The man I had once loved…</i>

246
00:18:06,376 --> 00:18:07,586
What is it?

247
00:18:08,587 --> 00:18:14,134
<i>Never returned to me</i>

248
00:18:16,512 --> 00:18:18,388
<i>And that was the time…</i>

249
00:18:18,472 --> 00:18:20,641
Stop it. We can't do this here.

250
00:18:21,350 --> 00:18:25,312
Come on. Doing it here makes it hot.

251
00:18:25,395 --> 00:18:27,147
You're high right now, aren't you?

252
00:18:28,398 --> 00:18:30,234
So what if I am?

253
00:18:30,317 --> 00:18:33,028
Come on. Stop it.
What's the matter with you?

254
00:18:33,529 --> 00:18:35,072
I said stop it!

255
00:18:43,247 --> 00:18:49,086
<i>And boarded another train</i>

256
00:18:50,003 --> 00:18:56,969
<i>My impoverished self</i>

257
00:18:58,804 --> 00:19:05,727
<i>Remains the same</i>

258
00:19:09,273 --> 00:19:16,238
<i>Someone please send word</i>

259
00:19:17,322 --> 00:19:22,911
<i>To my little sister</i>

260
00:19:24,079 --> 00:19:31,044
<i>That if she becomes like me</i>

261
00:19:32,754 --> 00:19:39,219
<i>That is the end</i>

262
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:55,360
I was flattered you finally asked.

263
00:19:57,738 --> 00:20:00,157
All right. Did you enjoy it?

264
00:20:00,240 --> 00:20:01,325
Yes, sir.

265
00:20:02,784 --> 00:20:04,328
Good. Let's get outta here.

266
00:20:05,037 --> 00:20:07,539
- Should we get another drink?
- Sure.

267
00:20:08,498 --> 00:20:09,917
Thank you very much.

268
00:20:10,959 --> 00:20:14,129
Yes. I wanted to discuss
this evening, actually.

269
00:20:22,512 --> 00:20:24,014
You were so charming.

270
00:20:24,097 --> 00:20:25,807
I don’t understand why…

271
00:21:23,991 --> 00:21:26,118
Did Takiguchi do something to you?

272
00:21:35,002 --> 00:21:37,421
How much debt do you have left, Kazuko?

273
00:21:39,881 --> 00:21:41,133
No idea.

274
00:21:42,009 --> 00:21:44,261
What do you mean you have no idea?

275
00:21:44,344 --> 00:21:46,972
No matter how much I pay,
it keeps growing.

276
00:21:48,557 --> 00:21:51,727
Apparently, another of Sudo's
promissory notes has turned up.

277
00:21:52,227 --> 00:21:53,854
Well, is that true?

278
00:21:53,937 --> 00:21:55,105
Of course not.

279
00:21:57,399 --> 00:21:59,735
He wants to keep me tied down
for the rest of my life.

280
00:22:03,363 --> 00:22:06,908
If I'd just died,
I wouldn't be in this mess.

281
00:22:18,712 --> 00:22:19,588
Listen.

282
00:22:21,590 --> 00:22:24,634
It's not all bad.
The debt collectors have gone away.

283
00:22:25,886 --> 00:22:28,722
And you're managing to live
a normal-enough life.

284
00:22:59,086 --> 00:23:04,174
FORTUNE-TELLING

285
00:23:10,806 --> 00:23:12,516
Hey!

286
00:23:13,350 --> 00:23:17,104
Can you cut it out with that crap?
I'm getting depressed. Play something fun!

287
00:23:17,187 --> 00:23:19,481
Don't you have something
to get us on our feet?

288
00:23:19,564 --> 00:23:21,608
Yeah, let's dance.

289
00:23:24,569 --> 00:23:26,363
That's enough music from you.

290
00:23:26,446 --> 00:23:28,448
Hey, old man! I'm talking to you!

291
00:23:28,532 --> 00:23:31,451
Take a walk and get off the stage!
Hey, old man!

292
00:23:31,535 --> 00:23:33,703
- I said get off, or I'll drag ya.
- All right, all of you.

293
00:23:33,787 --> 00:23:35,122
That's quite enough!

294
00:23:35,622 --> 00:23:37,249
You're disturbing my customers.

295
00:23:37,332 --> 00:23:40,168
So sorry, ma'am.
The boys got a little carried away.

296
00:23:40,752 --> 00:23:42,546
Yeah, we're real sorry.

297
00:23:43,880 --> 00:23:46,925
Please. Just keep it down, would you?

298
00:23:47,008 --> 00:23:49,970
Hey, old-timer.
Where you two sneaking off to?

299
00:23:50,053 --> 00:23:52,139
Oh.

300
00:23:52,931 --> 00:23:55,142
Sir. I'm so sorry about all that.

301
00:23:55,225 --> 00:23:57,477
Want me to tag along and give you a hand?

302
00:23:57,561 --> 00:23:59,563
This place has really gone to the dumps.

303
00:23:59,646 --> 00:24:01,231
I apologize, truly.

304
00:24:02,023 --> 00:24:04,568
Our deepest apologies, sir.

305
00:24:05,235 --> 00:24:06,903
It really has changed in here.

306
00:24:08,613 --> 00:24:10,198
This place used to be classy.

307
00:24:11,867 --> 00:24:13,118
Good evening, sir.

308
00:24:15,662 --> 00:24:17,873
I'm alone tonight. That okay?

309
00:24:18,373 --> 00:24:19,875
I should warn you.

310
00:24:19,958 --> 00:24:21,877
Some of the guests tonight

311
00:24:22,419 --> 00:24:25,046
have been rather disruptive
and unpleasant.

312
00:24:27,549 --> 00:24:28,717
Doesn't bother me.

313
00:24:30,469 --> 00:24:32,512
Then if you'll follow me.

314
00:24:44,774 --> 00:24:46,943
So sorry to interrupt your meal,

315
00:24:47,444 --> 00:24:49,654
but you were here the other day,
weren't you?

316
00:24:50,197 --> 00:24:51,114
Yes.

317
00:24:51,781 --> 00:24:55,827
I was a little tied up that day and didn't
have the chance to greet you. I'm sorry.

318
00:24:55,911 --> 00:24:58,330
I'm Kazuko Hosoki, the owner here.

319
00:24:58,830 --> 00:24:59,789
Hmm.

320
00:25:02,042 --> 00:25:03,084
I'm Hotta.

321
00:25:04,127 --> 00:25:06,171
This is one hell of a steak.

322
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:08,590
Thank you. I appreciate it.

323
00:25:08,673 --> 00:25:11,218
- I'm happy it was to your taste.
- I'm asking you to stop!

324
00:25:11,301 --> 00:25:14,804
Just calm down. My hand barely grazed you.
Don't make a fuss.

325
00:25:14,888 --> 00:25:16,473
- If you'll excuse me.
- That's not true.

326
00:25:16,556 --> 00:25:19,559
You calling me a liar?
You better watch it, you ugly bitch.

327
00:25:19,643 --> 00:25:23,021
Excuse me, sir, but I'm gonna have
to ask you to tone it down.

328
00:25:23,104 --> 00:25:24,856
- Tone down what exactly?
- I… Well, I…

329
00:25:24,940 --> 00:25:27,108
- What? You got something to say?
- What is it, Mitsuko?

330
00:25:27,192 --> 00:25:29,194
This man put his hands on me.

331
00:25:29,277 --> 00:25:31,029
Like I'd even be caught dead touching her.

332
00:25:31,112 --> 00:25:32,113
You can go.

333
00:25:34,991 --> 00:25:38,495
All right, that's enough.
You gentlemen have crossed the line.

334
00:25:38,578 --> 00:25:40,288
I'm sorry about all the ruckus.

335
00:25:40,372 --> 00:25:43,542
The boss gave the boys the green light
to let loose and have some fun tonight.

336
00:25:43,625 --> 00:25:46,378
- I apologize.
- I'm asking you to leave.

337
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:49,714
I have a feeling your boss
wouldn't be too happy with you

338
00:25:50,215 --> 00:25:51,591
if your behavior shut us down.

339
00:25:51,675 --> 00:25:52,676
Hang on.

340
00:25:53,260 --> 00:25:55,595
I take exception to what you just said.

341
00:25:57,847 --> 00:26:01,017
We're not living off the profits
of this club. Understood?

342
00:26:02,310 --> 00:26:05,146
And you should stop giving orders
above your position.

343
00:26:05,897 --> 00:26:08,108
The lady makes the rules here.

344
00:26:09,359 --> 00:26:11,236
If you don't like it, then you can leave.

345
00:26:12,612 --> 00:26:14,406
Who the hell do you think you are?

346
00:26:15,824 --> 00:26:16,825
Hotta.

347
00:26:17,534 --> 00:26:18,785
What are you doing here?

348
00:26:20,078 --> 00:26:21,997
I just came in to grab a bite.

349
00:26:23,331 --> 00:26:24,457
I see.

350
00:26:25,333 --> 00:26:27,210
Well, sorry for the ruckus.

351
00:26:27,711 --> 00:26:29,462
- Let's go.
- Huh?

352
00:26:29,546 --> 00:26:30,714
You heard me.

353
00:26:31,214 --> 00:26:32,090
Yeah.

354
00:26:42,642 --> 00:26:43,810
I'll go see them out.

355
00:26:49,566 --> 00:26:50,900
Thank you for that.

356
00:26:57,949 --> 00:26:59,659
I hope I wasn't out of line.

357
00:27:00,327 --> 00:27:01,161
Apologies.

358
00:27:03,121 --> 00:27:03,955
No.

359
00:27:40,033 --> 00:27:40,867
Yeah?

360
00:27:40,950 --> 00:27:43,203
<i>Minori, where the hell are you?</i>

361
00:27:43,286 --> 00:27:45,246
<i>- I've called you, like, six times!</i>
- Huh?

362
00:27:45,955 --> 00:27:47,791
<i>Where are you? Are you okay?</i>

363
00:27:47,874 --> 00:27:48,833
What?

364
00:27:54,798 --> 00:27:58,259
Isn't it Reina's visitation day today?
Did you forget?

365
00:27:58,343 --> 00:27:59,928
<i>Ah, shit.</i>

366
00:28:00,679 --> 00:28:03,264
<i>No, I didn't forget.</i>
<i>I just had a million things.</i>

367
00:28:03,348 --> 00:28:05,684
Grandma's gonna take me
so you don't have to.

368
00:28:05,767 --> 00:28:09,020
I'm gonna stay over at Daddy's house.

369
00:28:09,104 --> 00:28:11,690
Mommy, I hate you!

370
00:28:12,607 --> 00:28:14,526
You didn't tell me
you weren't coming home.

371
00:28:14,609 --> 00:28:16,444
Because that would've been good to know!

372
00:28:17,696 --> 00:28:19,989
Where are you? Don't say that

373
00:28:20,073 --> 00:28:21,991
<i>you're at some guy's place.</i>

374
00:28:22,075 --> 00:28:23,076
<i>Are you?</i>

375
00:28:24,327 --> 00:28:26,079
Look, Mom, I'll call you later.

376
00:28:53,356 --> 00:28:55,275
Oh, I know that look.

377
00:28:56,109 --> 00:28:59,904
Well, hardly shocking
after the amount you drank.

378
00:29:00,405 --> 00:29:04,451
Two full bottles of Dom Perignon.
500,000 yen a piece, I might add.

379
00:29:05,076 --> 00:29:06,745
I'm really sorry.

380
00:29:07,787 --> 00:29:09,789
Do you remember last night at all?

381
00:29:09,873 --> 00:29:11,624
It's kind of a blur.

382
00:29:11,708 --> 00:29:13,793
What's the last thing you remember?

383
00:29:14,502 --> 00:29:19,174
Uh, you saying,
"This is where I get revenge on men."

384
00:29:21,301 --> 00:29:24,971
Please, that's ridiculous.
What would I say that for?

385
00:29:25,472 --> 00:29:29,142
Even after all I've been through,
I still enjoy men even now.

386
00:29:30,560 --> 00:29:34,397
I was thinking I'd cook you something,
but I'm not sure you're up for it yet.

387
00:29:35,106 --> 00:29:37,066
Wait here. I'll make coffee.

388
00:29:38,777 --> 00:29:40,111
I'm so sorry.

389
00:30:06,679 --> 00:30:07,889
Is this…

390
00:30:20,109 --> 00:30:21,444
<i>Good evening. Welcome.</i>

391
00:30:28,535 --> 00:30:29,994
Thank you for coming in.

392
00:30:32,205 --> 00:30:33,998
These guys are with me.

393
00:30:34,499 --> 00:30:35,458
That all right?

394
00:30:36,793 --> 00:30:38,044
Of course it is.

395
00:31:18,293 --> 00:31:21,254
We very much appreciate
you joining us tonight.

396
00:31:22,046 --> 00:31:24,132
I hope you all enjoy yourselves.

397
00:31:25,383 --> 00:31:26,426
Thank you.

398
00:31:31,973 --> 00:31:34,809
Okay, this is bad.
I… I think that guy's a yakuza.

399
00:31:34,893 --> 00:31:37,645
Judging by last time, he doesn't seem
to get along with Takiguchi's lot.

400
00:31:37,729 --> 00:31:39,147
They just came in to eat.

401
00:31:39,230 --> 00:31:41,149
Yeah, but if Takiguchi finds out…

402
00:31:48,823 --> 00:31:49,949
Excuse me.

403
00:31:50,783 --> 00:31:51,826
Could I have this dance?

404
00:31:56,039 --> 00:31:59,042
You're aware, I'm sure,
that I'm Takiguchi's woman.

405
00:32:00,919 --> 00:32:03,129
I'm aware. Is that a problem?

406
00:32:06,341 --> 00:32:07,300
No.

407
00:32:45,672 --> 00:32:48,132
You're the head of the Edogawa family,
aren't you?

408
00:32:49,008 --> 00:32:50,426
Masaya Hotta.

409
00:32:52,679 --> 00:32:57,058
Should we… talk about that
elsewhere, perhaps?

410
00:32:57,600 --> 00:32:59,185
What are you trying to do here?

411
00:33:00,228 --> 00:33:02,105
This place is my cage.

412
00:33:02,981 --> 00:33:07,068
And the only freedom I have
is inside this cage

413
00:33:08,152 --> 00:33:10,279
because my owner's terrifying.

414
00:33:14,409 --> 00:33:17,745
What if… you were able to get out?

415
00:33:22,125 --> 00:33:23,835
If you could get outta here,

416
00:33:25,253 --> 00:33:26,379
would you do it?

417
00:33:41,978 --> 00:33:46,399
No, please, don't stop on my account.
My, what a cute couple you make.

418
00:33:49,569 --> 00:33:50,737
You must be Hotta, right?

419
00:33:51,821 --> 00:33:56,159
Word is you're a gambling man
who's already head of his own family.

420
00:33:56,242 --> 00:33:57,702
Impressive.

421
00:33:58,745 --> 00:34:00,580
Takiguchi-san.

422
00:34:00,663 --> 00:34:03,583
I heard you made quite a name
for yourself back in the day.

423
00:34:05,585 --> 00:34:09,005
It seems like you're a regular here now.

424
00:34:09,589 --> 00:34:11,758
Yeah, the rib eye here is to die for.

425
00:34:12,467 --> 00:34:14,469
I wanted my men to give it a try.

426
00:34:17,096 --> 00:34:18,264
And besides…

427
00:34:19,223 --> 00:34:20,391
And besides, what?

428
00:34:24,562 --> 00:34:26,397
I'm rather taken with the owner.

429
00:34:39,327 --> 00:34:42,288
You hear that, Kazuko? He likes ya!

430
00:34:46,042 --> 00:34:47,752
Stay as long as you like.

431
00:34:48,252 --> 00:34:50,171
I'll cover your table tonight.

432
00:34:56,260 --> 00:34:57,762
Takiguchi-san.

433
00:34:59,597 --> 00:35:01,641
I'm opening a game next week.

434
00:35:02,475 --> 00:35:04,143
I'd be honored if you joined.

435
00:35:06,562 --> 00:35:07,772
All right, then.

436
00:35:08,481 --> 00:35:10,191
I look forward to it.

437
00:35:12,235 --> 00:35:13,611
I'll be expecting you.

438
00:35:36,884 --> 00:35:39,595
Whoring around, right under my nose?

439
00:35:40,680 --> 00:35:42,682
You're mine, you got that?

440
00:35:47,645 --> 00:35:49,188
That little

441
00:35:50,064 --> 00:35:51,566
piece of shit!

442
00:35:53,526 --> 00:35:55,361
That son of a bitch!

443
00:36:06,539 --> 00:36:08,499
All right! Go ahead, place your bets!

444
00:36:08,583 --> 00:36:10,209
Place your bets.
Go ahead. Place your bets.

445
00:36:10,293 --> 00:36:12,170
Place your bets. Thank you, sir.
Place your bets.

446
00:36:12,253 --> 00:36:14,046
Go ahead. Anyone else? Place your bets.

447
00:36:14,130 --> 00:36:16,174
Anyone else? Go on. Place your bets.

448
00:36:16,257 --> 00:36:18,176
Place your bets. Go on, place your bets.

449
00:36:18,259 --> 00:36:19,927
Place your bets. Right here.

450
00:36:20,011 --> 00:36:21,262
- Thank you.
- No more bets.

451
00:36:22,805 --> 00:36:24,098
All set, gentlemen.

452
00:36:25,099 --> 00:36:26,100
Showdown!

453
00:36:29,770 --> 00:36:32,315
And the card is a six! Six!
Anyone with a six, open it!

454
00:36:32,398 --> 00:36:34,150
Open on six. Open if you have a six.

455
00:36:34,233 --> 00:36:35,151
Well done, sir.

456
00:36:35,234 --> 00:36:37,403
Here you are. Thank you.

457
00:36:38,613 --> 00:36:39,530
Thank you, sir.

458
00:36:49,874 --> 00:36:51,834
- Right this way.
- Thank you.

459
00:37:37,046 --> 00:37:38,130
Back to one.

460
00:38:02,363 --> 00:38:04,699
Okay, it's in. Place your bets.
Go on, place your bets.

461
00:38:04,782 --> 00:38:06,784
Gentlemen, go on. Go on, place your bets.

462
00:38:06,867 --> 00:38:08,577
- Place your bets.
- Place your bets.

463
00:38:08,661 --> 00:38:10,288
Place your bets. Place your bets.

464
00:38:10,955 --> 00:38:12,665
- All right, done.
- Done. That's done.

465
00:38:12,748 --> 00:38:13,833
All set.

466
00:38:13,916 --> 00:38:14,792
Okay.

467
00:38:16,043 --> 00:38:17,211
All set here too.

468
00:38:17,753 --> 00:38:18,713
Showdown!

469
00:38:24,468 --> 00:38:26,304
First card's a five.
Five is the first card.

470
00:38:26,387 --> 00:38:27,596
Open it if you have a five.

471
00:38:27,680 --> 00:38:29,765
Open if you have a five, gentlemen.

472
00:38:29,849 --> 00:38:30,725
Five.

473
00:38:31,225 --> 00:38:33,019
- Here you are, sir.
- Thank you.

474
00:38:33,894 --> 00:38:35,688
Anyone on five, collect.
Open if you have five.

475
00:38:35,771 --> 00:38:37,481
Open if you have five.

476
00:38:39,567 --> 00:38:41,027
- Here you go.
- Thank you, sir.

477
00:38:41,110 --> 00:38:42,153
All right.

478
00:38:46,032 --> 00:38:48,617
- Get new shoes.
- Not with your luck.

479
00:38:54,540 --> 00:38:55,583
Back to one.

480
00:38:58,336 --> 00:39:00,129
All right, here we go. Place your bets.

481
00:39:00,212 --> 00:39:02,673
There we go. Place your bets.
Place your bets, go ahead.

482
00:39:02,757 --> 00:39:04,633
Place your bets. Go on, place your bets.

483
00:39:04,717 --> 00:39:06,719
Come on, place your bets. Go on.

484
00:39:06,802 --> 00:39:08,637
Once you're set, hands off. Any more?

485
00:39:08,721 --> 00:39:10,222
Last call for bets?

486
00:39:14,268 --> 00:39:15,770
All set here.

487
00:39:15,853 --> 00:39:16,979
Showdown!

488
00:39:20,524 --> 00:39:22,318
The second card is two. Open on two.

489
00:39:22,401 --> 00:39:24,028
Card is two. Open on two.

490
00:39:24,111 --> 00:39:25,738
If you're not on two, pull your card.

491
00:39:25,821 --> 00:39:27,573
- Open on two.
- Thank you, sir.

492
00:39:27,656 --> 00:39:29,742
- If you're on two, open it.
- Thank you.

493
00:39:29,825 --> 00:39:31,619
Second card is two.

494
00:39:31,702 --> 00:39:33,079
- Thank you.
- Okay.

495
00:39:37,416 --> 00:39:39,668
The middle card is four. Anyone on four?

496
00:39:39,752 --> 00:39:41,629
Open on four.

497
00:39:45,132 --> 00:39:47,259
The second card is five. Payout on five.

498
00:39:47,343 --> 00:39:48,969
If you're on five, open it. Card is five.

499
00:39:49,053 --> 00:39:50,179
Middle card is five.

500
00:39:52,306 --> 00:39:54,183
First card is three. First card is three.

501
00:39:54,266 --> 00:39:56,811
Okay, three collects.
If you're on three, open it.

502
00:39:56,894 --> 00:39:59,146
Here you go. Thank you, sir.

503
00:39:59,230 --> 00:40:01,315
Collect on three.
Open it if you're on three.

504
00:40:19,583 --> 00:40:20,960
- Boss.
- Finally!

505
00:40:21,043 --> 00:40:22,253
I'm sorry, sir.

506
00:40:26,632 --> 00:40:27,466
Here.

507
00:40:37,268 --> 00:40:38,602
Then back to one.

508
00:40:59,415 --> 00:41:02,376
- Place your bets, please.
- Place your bets. Place your bets.

509
00:41:02,460 --> 00:41:04,044
If you're set, hands off, please.

510
00:41:04,128 --> 00:41:05,796
All right, all set over here.

511
00:41:05,880 --> 00:41:07,006
Anyone else?

512
00:41:08,549 --> 00:41:10,968
Any last bets? Place your bets now.

513
00:41:14,096 --> 00:41:15,347
Middle card is five.

514
00:41:15,431 --> 00:41:17,683
- Collect on five.
- If you're on five, open it.

515
00:41:17,766 --> 00:41:19,268
Middle card is five.

516
00:41:19,351 --> 00:41:20,603
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

517
00:41:27,359 --> 00:41:28,402
Back to one.

518
00:41:51,634 --> 00:41:52,551
And it's in.

519
00:42:15,991 --> 00:42:16,909
All set.

520
00:42:19,995 --> 00:42:21,080
Showdown.

521
00:42:29,713 --> 00:42:31,131
The card is six.

522
00:42:43,477 --> 00:42:45,312
I think that's enough.

523
00:42:45,396 --> 00:42:47,022
Wait, I'm not done yet.

524
00:42:48,107 --> 00:42:49,233
Please, boss.

525
00:42:49,316 --> 00:42:50,484
Quiet!

526
00:42:55,990 --> 00:42:56,949
Hang on.

527
00:43:27,855 --> 00:43:30,149
- Oh.
- About time!

528
00:43:39,533 --> 00:43:41,076
Is that all you've got?

529
00:43:41,160 --> 00:43:42,870
It's the middle of the night.

530
00:43:43,454 --> 00:43:45,789
I'm sorry,
but that's all I have right now.

531
00:44:02,014 --> 00:44:03,057
Back to one.

532
00:44:28,624 --> 00:44:29,750
And it's in.

533
00:44:55,067 --> 00:44:56,902
With such a small bet,

534
00:44:57,403 --> 00:45:00,406
even if you run the board,
you won't make up what you lost.

535
00:45:15,963 --> 00:45:17,339
I can spot you.

536
00:45:37,818 --> 00:45:38,944
Showdown.

537
00:45:45,200 --> 00:45:46,702
The second card, one.

538
00:46:43,759 --> 00:46:45,636
It's the deed to this place.

539
00:46:46,136 --> 00:46:49,598
He gave it to me
as collateral for his debt.

540
00:46:50,891 --> 00:46:52,226
It's all yours now.

541
00:46:58,398 --> 00:47:00,234
Why give it to me?

542
00:47:00,984 --> 00:47:04,071
Takiguchi… walked right into my trap.

543
00:47:04,154 --> 00:47:07,950
He let his jealousy get the best of him,
and he lost.

544
00:47:09,409 --> 00:47:10,410
And that's it.

545
00:47:12,371 --> 00:47:14,540
I used you to get to him.

546
00:47:15,541 --> 00:47:17,000
Consider it a thank-you.

547
00:47:18,043 --> 00:47:20,170
You used me to get to him?

548
00:47:23,340 --> 00:47:24,174
Yeah.

549
00:47:27,594 --> 00:47:29,638
It's been over a week since then,

550
00:47:29,721 --> 00:47:31,890
and he hasn't tried to contact me.

551
00:47:32,975 --> 00:47:34,518
Do you know why that is?

552
00:47:35,394 --> 00:47:38,897
Takiguchi is no longer welcome
in the Kosei-kai.

553
00:47:39,398 --> 00:47:42,025
They found out
he was making his money off crystals,

554
00:47:43,026 --> 00:47:44,653
and he was kicked out of Tokyo.

555
00:47:45,571 --> 00:47:47,281
The man's finished, Kazuko.

556
00:47:51,660 --> 00:47:52,953
You're free now.

557
00:47:53,787 --> 00:47:56,748
Out of that cage, just like you wanted.

558
00:48:00,669 --> 00:48:01,795
You did all this for me?

559
00:48:01,879 --> 00:48:03,380
It was more than that.

560
00:48:05,257 --> 00:48:06,758
It was a decision

561
00:48:07,843 --> 00:48:09,052
made by the yakuza.

562
00:48:13,140 --> 00:48:14,349
It's been a pleasure.

563
00:48:16,184 --> 00:48:17,102
Have a good life.

564
00:48:18,145 --> 00:48:19,438
No, wait.

565
00:48:20,188 --> 00:48:21,940
Hold on a minute, will you?

566
00:48:33,327 --> 00:48:36,496
After so many men had screwed me over,

567
00:48:37,789 --> 00:48:39,708
I finally found it.

568
00:48:39,791 --> 00:48:41,793
I finally found real love.

569
00:48:47,090 --> 00:48:50,761
Loneliness can make people
fall madly in love with each other.

570
00:48:51,637 --> 00:48:52,804
In the <i>Manyoshu,</i>

571
00:48:52,888 --> 00:48:56,350
they wrote the word love as "ko-hi,"
which combines the "ko" and "hi" of kanji,

572
00:48:56,433 --> 00:48:57,559
for loneliness and sadness.

573
00:48:57,643 --> 00:48:58,560
Did you know that?

574
00:48:58,644 --> 00:48:59,519
I didn't.

575
00:48:59,603 --> 00:49:03,482
And you call yourself a novelist,
not knowing something like that?

576
00:49:04,942 --> 00:49:06,234
Do you have a pen?

577
00:49:06,985 --> 00:49:07,945
Uh…

578
00:49:18,789 --> 00:49:23,627
In the old days, people better understood
the true nature of things, didn't they?

579
00:49:27,297 --> 00:49:29,383
"Loneliness" and "sadness."

580
00:49:30,467 --> 00:49:31,385
"Love."

581
00:49:32,552 --> 00:49:35,138
Have you ever experienced
anything like that?

582
00:49:37,724 --> 00:49:39,726
How do you think
you're going to write a great novel

583
00:49:39,810 --> 00:49:41,353
without ever knowing true love?

584
00:49:42,771 --> 00:49:43,689
Mm.

585
00:49:46,900 --> 00:49:50,696
So, you and Hotta.
What happened after that?

586
00:50:40,120 --> 00:50:45,375
<i>Each place I go…</i>

587
00:50:45,459 --> 00:50:47,294
I hope you enjoy your evening.

588
00:50:47,377 --> 00:50:48,628
- Very much.
- Excuse me, please.

589
00:50:48,712 --> 00:50:50,380
Of course. Thank you.

590
00:50:53,759 --> 00:50:59,181
<i>Some little small</i>

591
00:51:00,849 --> 00:51:03,602
<i>Café</i>

592
00:51:05,062 --> 00:51:10,108
<i>The songs I know</i>

593
00:51:10,609 --> 00:51:16,615
<i>Only the lonely know</i>

594
00:51:17,199 --> 00:51:21,161
<i>Each melody</i>

595
00:51:22,370 --> 00:51:25,373
<i>Recalls a love</i>

596
00:51:25,457 --> 00:51:26,666
EDOGAWA-IKKA FAMILY

597
00:51:26,750 --> 00:51:29,169
<i>That used to be</i>

598
00:51:29,252 --> 00:51:35,592
<i>The dreams I dream</i>

599
00:51:36,510 --> 00:51:42,349
<i>Only the lonely dream</i>

600
00:51:43,350 --> 00:51:45,894
<i>Of lips</i>

601
00:51:45,977 --> 00:51:52,943
<i>As warm as May</i>

602
00:51:54,194 --> 00:51:58,782
<i>That hopeless scheme</i>

603
00:51:59,991 --> 00:52:05,956
<i>Only the lonely scheme</i>

604
00:52:06,706 --> 00:52:10,919
<i>That soon somewhere</i>

605
00:52:12,504 --> 00:52:18,260
<i>You'll find the one that used to care</i>

606
00:52:18,885 --> 00:52:24,724
<i>And you recall</i>

607
00:52:24,808 --> 00:52:27,936
<i>Each fun time</i>

608
00:52:29,104 --> 00:52:33,108
<i>Those picnics at the beach</i>

609
00:52:33,191 --> 00:52:37,070
<i>When love was new…</i>

610
00:52:51,626 --> 00:52:53,378
Let me through, please!

611
00:52:53,920 --> 00:52:55,964
- Move!
- You need to go now!

612
00:52:57,507 --> 00:52:58,425
Boss.

613
00:52:59,050 --> 00:53:01,386
Please! Get off me!

614
00:53:07,893 --> 00:53:08,727
It's all right.

615
00:53:27,704 --> 00:53:29,122
What are you doing here?

616
00:53:30,207 --> 00:53:31,708
You're a coward!

617
00:53:32,292 --> 00:53:34,753
I can't be the only one
who feels this way!

618
00:53:37,672 --> 00:53:40,550
I'm a yakuza.
I'm no different than Takiguchi.

619
00:53:41,718 --> 00:53:43,929
Nothing good would come
of us being together.

620
00:53:44,512 --> 00:53:48,016
Oh, stop it with the tough guy shit!

621
00:53:49,184 --> 00:53:51,019
I want to be with you.

622
00:53:52,062 --> 00:53:54,272
And you want me too. I know you do.

623
00:53:56,066 --> 00:53:57,525
Make love to me.

624
00:53:58,735 --> 00:54:00,320
Come on. Make love to me!

625
00:55:22,736 --> 00:55:24,446
I loved Masaya,

626
00:55:25,739 --> 00:55:27,741
and he loved me too.
